Comment.Text: * Find a Console in the Schedule Area* If no console can be found in the Schedule Area, then search nearby* Use DownloadData use channel on the console* While using the console search for a sub-component with the 'damaged' game tag applied* Execute the ExecuteEngineeringTask sub activity ensuring it uses the found damaged sub-component* If no damaged sub-component is found, then find a wallpanel within the Schedule Area to inspect* If no wallpanel is found within the Schedule Area then find one nearby
Find a Console usable. First search the schedule area. If none are found then search in the immediate area around the NPC.If no Consoles are found then skip using a Console entirely.
Perform the "DownloadData" use channel on the Console that was just found. This will cause the NPC to pull out their datapad and "download the task data" to their datapad.
Perform the "DownloadData" use channel for 5 seconds (variation of 1).

Check to make sure the NPC has a Datapad equipped in their current loadout. If a Datapad is found then perform "DownloadData" use channel on the Console. If no Datapad is found then perform the "Type" use channel on the console instead.
Perform the "Type" use channel on the Console that was just found. This will cause the NPC to type on the usable.
Perform the "Type" use channel for 5 seconds (variation of 1).
Search the ScheduleArea for a Console usable. If one isn't found then move onto searching the immediate area.
Search the immediate area for a Console usable.
Randomly select between finding usables to use.If one fails then move onto the next.If all fail then use failsafe logic.
Randomly select between Taking a Break, Talking to a colleague and Taking a Stroll
FailSafe logic - This should only occur when the engineer is unable to find a Wallpanel or Workzone to maintain.
Execute the engineering task that has been defined in this activity.
Empty all object and usable variables
Ensure NPC is wearing work outfit
Ensure NPC is wearing welding helmet outfit
